KNN Model

five_fold_knn = function(data, y, k, seed){
  #Setting up cross validation
  set.seed(seed)
  len = nrow(data)
  index = sample(1:len)
  size = floor(len / 5)
  #shuffling the data
  x = data[index,]
  y = y[index]
  #looping through each k
  #vector of missclassified data count and accuracy
  miss = c()
  acc = c()
  #separating the data
  count = 1
  for(i in 1:5)
  {
    if(i != 5)
    {
      test.x = x[count:(count + size),]
      test.y = y[count:(count + size)]
      train.x = x[-(count:(count + size)),]
      train.y = y[-(count:(count + size))]
    }
    else
    {
      test.x = x[count:len,]
      test.y = y[count:len]
      train.x = x[-(count:len),]
      train.y = y[-(count:len)]
    }
    count = count + size
    #Performing knn for k
    mod = knn(train = train.x, test = test.x, cl = train.y, k = k)
    #Finding missclassification
    vect = c()
    count = 1
    error = 0
    for(j in mod){
      if(j != test.y[count]){
        error = error + 1
      }
      count = count + 1
    }
    miss[i] = error
    acc[i] = (length(mod) - error) / length(mod)
  }
  avg.miss = mean(miss)
  avg.acc = mean(acc)
  return(c(avg.miss,avg.acc))
}
#subsetting the data
knn.predictors = c("nscore","escore","oscore","ascore","cscore")
drug.knn = drug[knn.predictors]

knn.response = c("sched_1","sched_2","sched_3","sched_4",
             "stimulant","depressant","hallucinogen","stimulant_nc")
drug.response = drug[knn.response]
#Error plots for each response
par(mfrow=c(1,2), mar=c(4,4,2,0.5))
for(i in 1:length(knn.response)){
  y = drug.response[[i]]
  avg.miss = c()
  avg.acc = c()
  for( k in 1:round(sqrt(nrow(drug)))){
  results = five_fold_knn(data = drug.knn,y = y,k = k,seed = 1234)
  avg.miss[k] = results[1]
  avg.acc[k] = results[2]
  }
  plot(1:round(sqrt(nrow(drug))),avg.miss,ylab = "Test Error", xlab = "K Value",
       main = paste("Test Error Plot of",knn.response[i]))
  plot(1:round(sqrt(nrow(drug))),avg.acc,ylab = "Test Accuracy", 
       xlab = "K Value",main = paste("Test Accuracy Plot of",knn.response[i]))
}
